ENTRY       EC 6.2.1.40                 Enzyme
NAME        4-hydroxybutyrate---CoA ligase;
            4-hydroxybutyrate-CoA synthetase
CLASS       Ligases;
            Forming carbon-sulfur bonds;
            Acid-thiol ligases
SYSNAME     4-hydroxybutyrate:CoA ligase (AMP formimg)
REACTION    ATP + 4-hydroxybutanoate + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + 4-hydroxybutanoyl-CoA
SUBSTRATE   ATP [CPD:C00002];
            4-hydroxybutanoate [CPD:C00989];
            CoA [CPD:C00010]
PRODUCT     AMP [CPD:C00020];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013];
            4-hydroxybutanoyl-CoA [CPD:C11062]
COMMENT     Isolated from the archaeon Metallosphaera sedula. Involved in the 3-hydroxypropionate/4-hydroxybutyrate cycle.
